        "title": "Add Gateway system.run MXC runtime E2E proof",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nPR3 for #784. This adds a focused runtime proof for the real Gateway path:\n\nGateway -> node.invoke -> Windows node -> system.run -> MXC process containment.\n\nThis is intentionally stacked after #786. A focused compare for the PR3 delta is:\nhttps://github.com/TheAngryPit/openclaw-windows-node/compare/feature/mxc-26200-sdk-0-7-validation...feature/gateway-system-run-mxc-e2e\n\n## What changed\n\n- Adds `RealGateway_SystemRun_ExecutesThroughWindowsNodeMxcSandbox` to the E2E setup suite.\n- Moves the MXC proof into its own gated E2E MXC Setup collection so non-MXC runners skip before heavy setup.\n- The test provisions a fresh WSL Gateway, starts an isolated tray instance, sets a local exec approval through MCP, invokes `system.run` through `openclaw gateway call node.invoke`, and verifies MXC diagnostics in the tray log.\n- The test asserts `gateway.nodes.allowCommands` includes `system.run`, `system.run.prepare`, and `system.which` before invoking the proof path.\n- Documents the focused runtime proof command and required evidence markers in `docs/WINDOWS_NODE_TESTING.md`.\n\n## Validation\n\nFinal-head validation for commit `cad71667` on Windows build `26200.8728`:\n\n- `dotnet test tests\\OpenClaw.Shared.Tests\\OpenClaw.Shared.Tests.csproj --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~MxcCommandRunnerTests|FullyQualifiedName~MxcConfigBuilderTests\" --no-restore --verbosity minimal` passed: `66` passed, `0` failed.\n- `dotnet test tests\\OpenClaw.Tray.Tests\\OpenClaw.Tray.Tests.csproj --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~SettingsRoundTripTests\" --no-restore --verbosity minimal` passed: `18` passed, `0` failed.\n- `dotnet test tests\\OpenClaw.E2ETests\\OpenClaw.E2ETests.csproj --no-restore --list-tests --verbosity minimal` passed compile/listing and listed `OpenClaw.E2ETests.Setup.MxcSetupAndConnectTests.RealGateway_SystemRun_ExecutesThroughWindowsNodeMxcSandbox`.\n- `dotnet restore src\\OpenClaw.Tray.WinUI\\OpenClaw.Tray.WinUI.csproj -r win-x64` followed by `dotnet build src\\OpenClaw.Tray.WinUI\\OpenClaw.Tray.WinUI.csproj --no-restore --configuration Debug --runtime win-x64 --verbosity minimal` passed: `0` warnings, `0` errors.\n- Real MXC Gateway E2E passed on final head:\n  - `$env:OPENCLAW_REPO_ROOT=(Get-Location).Path`\n  - `$env:OPENCLAW_RUN_E2E=\"1\"`\n  - `dotnet test .\\tests\\OpenClaw.E2ETests\\OpenClaw.E2ETests.csproj --no-restore --configuration Debug --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~RealGateway_SystemRun_ExecutesThroughWindowsNodeMxcSandbox\" --logger \"trx;LogFileName=pr3-mxc-e2e-final.trx\" --verbosity minimal`\n  - Result: `1` passed, `0` failed, `0` skipped.\n- Runtime proof markers from `pr3-mxc-e2e-final.trx`:\n  - `gateway.nodes.allowCommands includes system.run/system.run.prepare/system.which`\n  - `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_SYSTEM_RUN_MXC_OK`\n  - `exitCode=0`\n  - `executor=mxc-direct-appc`\n  - `contained=True`\n  - `shell=cmd`\n  - `systemRunBlockHostFallbackWhenMxcUnavailable=true`\n  - `containment=mxc`\n  - `stderrChars=0`\n- `openclaw-autoreview --mode branch --base local-pr2/feature-mxc-26200-sdk-0-7-validation --engine codex --model gpt-5.5 --thinking high` ended clean: no accepted/actionable findings, overall `patch is correct`.\n\n## Notes\n\nThis proves the Gateway/Windows-node/MXC runtime path on top of the current PR2 fail-closed default. It does not claim proof of installed Companion replacement/profile migration.\n\nRefs #784\nStacked after #786\n",
